x4freetext: Pd-300 neutron generator
Approximately 15 g of high purity BaCO3 powder (99.99%
pure) was pressed at 980 MPa, and a pellet around 0.4
cm thick and 2.0 cm in diameter was obtained. Three
such pellets were prepared.
Monitor foils (Nb, 99.99% pure, 0.5 mm thick) of the
same diameter as the pellets were then attached in
front and at the back of each sample.
Neutrons were produced with an effective
deuteron beam energy and current of 135 keV and 260
uA. The T-Ti target has a thickness of 2.4 mg/cm2 and
the diameter of the active zone is 1.2 cm.
The crystal geometry is 70.1 x 72.3 mm in
diameter and length. The relative efficiency is about
68%, and energy resolution is 1.69 keV at 1332 keV
gamma ray from Co-60. The efficiency of the detector
was pre-calibrated using various standard gamma
sources, which were Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109, Ba-133,
The Au-Si surface barrier detector used in
the 135-deg accompanying alpha-particle tube was 110
cm from the target.
Irradiation of the samples was lasted about
117 min with a yield around 3 to 4E10 n/(4pi*s). The
groups of sample were placed at 0, 90 or 135 degree
relative to the beam direction and centered about the
T-Ti target at distances of around 40 mm.
During irradiation, the neutron flux was monitored by
accompanying alpha particles so that corrections
could be made for small variations in the yield.
The self-absorption of the sample at a given gamma
energy, in the counting geometry, and the coincidence
sum effect of cascade gamma rays in the investigated
nuclide were corrected.
Total uncertainty
Counting statistics 0.1-6.5%
Detector efficiency 2-3.0%
Weight of samples 0.1%
Self-absorption of gamma-ray 1%
Cooling and measuring times 0.1-1%
Uncertainties in branching ratio of
the characteristic gamma rays 0.2-1.4%
Uncertainties in the half-lives of
the radioactive product nuclei 0.1-1.4%
Abundance of the target isotope 0.8-
Standard cross sections uncertainties 1.5%
Data were obtained from TABLE 4 of
J,Radiochim.Acta,105,779,2017
Compiled by Haijing Jin (CNDC)
Contribution of the metastable state decay were
subtracted.
